x4freetext: The 17.7 and 20.9 MeV runs were made with
Mobley Magnet Facility at Los Alamos Van de Graaff.
C4,36,1971) were re-evaluated. It was found that in the
earlier results (given in subentry 2) the correction
for multiple scattering effects had been over-estimated
by an order of magnitude. Using a recent neutron
transport code (MCNPX), a new simulation calculation
Complete documentation of the 1970 experiment made
additional improvements of the data possible, resulting
in particular in more precise values of the incident
See details of partial uncertainties in Table III
Scale uncertainty, correlated between all data
points of the same beam energy
